para_trans: GOVERNMENT ORDER NUMBER: USP 1324 / P.No.102 / PRASH-1
Madam Cama Marg, Martyrdom Rajguru Chowk,
Reference: - MIN 1224 / Q. No. 146 / MASTA-1, D. 28.11.2024

The officer was awaiting appointment after the following officers of the Deputy Secretary cadre, who were deputed to the office establishment of the Hon'ble Chief Minister / Hon'ble Minister as per the order under the aforesaid context, were repatriated due to non-availability of posts in the parent department.
2. Now, the post-retirement posting of these officers is as follows: Column No. 4 is being done as mentioned.
3. The officers mentioned above should join the department in which they have been posted immediately.

The period from the date of the said Deputy Secretary's return from the post of Service Deputation to the date of this Order is being regulated as compulsory waiting in accordance with Rule 9 (14) (f) (ii) of the M.N.S. (General Conditions of Service) Rules, 1981.
The Government Order is available on the Government of Maharashtra website www.maharashtra.gov.in.
